There are 3 types of APFNxx00 programs. 
	1. Collection processors
	2. Object processors
	3. Exception Collection processors (so far CM and SP)
	
FNxx collection processor programs 
Function code driven.  Effect workClient action based on function

If  inputFunctionCode = U
    findMatching() (note - findMatching will no longer remove segments when a match is found)
    
    if  matchSW
        if inputAction = 0 or V
           set inputActionCode to V
           remove work
           add input to work
           
        else if  inputAction = C or A
                 remove work
                 set inputActionCode to C
                 add input to work
                 process edit
                     
        else (must be D)
             set workActionCode to D
    
    else
        set inputActionCode to A
        Add input to work
        process edit
        
FNxx object processor programs
Function code driven.  Effect workClient action based on function

If  inputFunctionCode = U
	if work == null
		set inputActionCode to A
		set work to input
		processEdits
	else if action = 0 or V
		set inputActionCode to V
		set work to input
	else if action = A or C or D
		set work to input
		process edits

FNxx Exception Collection processor (CM/SP) programs

if input != null
	'clear()' work
	loop thru input 
		setActionCode('A')
		setFunctionCode('U')
		add input to work
else
if work != null
	loop thru work
		setActionCode('D')
		setFunctionCode('U')
		

NExx basic program rules (more complex rules may exist)
Action code driven.  Effect workClient based on action code

if  workAction = A or C
    edit
    set workAction to 0
else if  workAction = V
         verify against disk
         set workAction to 0
     else if  workAction = D
              remove from work
              
NCxx programs.  These programs look at the segment in relation to the record.
They deal with workClient.  